What matters is #Bitcoin can be transferred for value without an intermediary. These two advancements are critical to censorship resistance.  At least that's my 3 cents.

While store of value is fundamental to #Bitcoin, it only resonates with those who have been battered by inflation.  So many in the Western world have had the trickle impact of inflation... so much so they know something isn't right but cannot comprehend the root cause.

It is a true chicken/egg conundrum... because of #Bitcoin's strong monetary properties, we use it as a last resort; unfortunately, in many parts of the world, that last resort comes when traditional financial systems have been shuttered.
Until #Bitcoin nullifies the need to utilize centralized exchanges for fiat exchange and access to the broader financial community, its censorship resistance is severely limited.

#Bitcoin 's great property as a store of value in some ways is limiting the urgency by companies to feel obligated to accept it...it is rarely used.  This is why El Salvador's legal tender adoption and emergence of #LightningNetwork  were such  giant leaps forward.
If #Bitcoin is to be considered censorship resistance, it cannot attain all its status as a store of value.  It must be person to person, entity to entity and particularly, person to business.
